Key Match Events: Namibia beat Oman in the third match of the 2024 T20 World Cup after a Super Over.
David Wiese performed exceptionally in the Super Over with both bat and ball to win the game for Namibia.
Oman was bundled out for 109 in 19.4 overs with Khalid Kail top-scoring with 34 runs.
Ruben Trumpelmann took 4 wickets for 21 runs and David Wiese took 3 wickets for 28 runs for Namibia.
Mehran Khan bowled a sensational spell of 3-1-7-3 for Oman.
Jan Frylinck scored 45 runs for Namibia.
Namibia scored 21 runs in the Super Over with contributions from David Wiese and Gerhard Erasmus.
David Wiese conceded only 10 runs in the Super Over, defending the target successfully.
Post-Match Reflections: Namibia captain Gerhard Erasmus expressed relief and pleasure at winning the match, acknowledging the difficulty of batting on the pitch.
Erasmus praised Jan Frylinck's important contribution and David Wiese's performance in the Super Over.
Erasmus hoped that the winning momentum would continue in the World Cup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The low-scoring thriller between Namibia and Oman entertained fans, who shared hilarious memes on social media.
